==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peerage
<hw>Peer"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Peer</er> an
equal, and cf. <er>Parage</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The rank or
dignity of a peer.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The body of peers; the nobility,
collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When Charlemain with all his <qex>peerage</qex> fell.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peerdom</ent>⟦br⟧
